          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-09-13 17:02:41" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to be happy about something, on the basis that it would prove particularly welcome (thus implying a type of future orientation)</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to be happy about</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to anticipate with pleasure</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In order to render the future implications of ἀσπάζομαι in {S:05801101300030}, one may be able to translate ‘and looked forward with happiness to what was going to happen.’ For another interpretation of ἀσπάζομαι in {S:05801101300030}, see ἀσπάζομαι[c] {D:34.55}.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
