            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-09-13 17:02:41" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>to welcome something or someone, with focus upon the initial greeting</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to welcome</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to accept gladly</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In some languages, however, it may be difficult to speak of ‘welcoming promises,’ but one can often render this relationship as ‘they were happy to know about what had been promised.’ For another interpretation of ἀσπάζομαι in {S:05801101300030}, see ἀσπάζομαι[b] {D:25.130}.</Comments>
